## Quick Copy Commands

### Desktop Setup (Primary)
```bash
# Hyprland configs
cp desktop/conf/hypr/* /home/owner/.config/hypr/

# Scripts
cp desktop/bin/* /home/owner/bin/

# Waybar configs
cp desktop/conf/waybar/* /home/owner/.config/waybar/

# Kitty configs
cp desktop/conf/kitty/* /home/owner/.config/kitty/

# Eww configs
cp desktop/eww/* /home/owner/.config/eww/
```

### TV Setup (Alternative)
```bash
# TV-specific Hyprland configs (rename to avoid conflicts)
cp tv/conf/hypr/autostart.conf /home/owner/.config/hypr/autostart-tv.conf
cp tv/conf/hypr/bindings.conf /home/owner/.config/hypr/bindings-tv.conf
# ... etc for all TV configs

# TV-specific scripts (rename to avoid conflicts)
cp tv/bin/cycle-apps /home/owner/bin/cycle-apps-tv
cp tv/bin/workspace-nav /home/owner/bin/workspace-nav-tv
# ... etc
```

## Key Mapping Notes

- **Desktop configs** go directly to standard locations (e.g., `~/.config/hypr/`)
- **TV configs** should be renamed with `-tv` suffix to avoid conflicts
- **Scripts** can go directly to `~/bin/` or be renamed for TV variants
- **Repository is the source of truth** - always copy FROM repo TO system
